  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1301788874" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1301788874" />
    <a title="Albert" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18868296-albert"><img alt="Albert" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1574953891p2/18868296.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1301788874?book_show_action=true">Jan 01, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Albert" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Albert" href="/user/show/18868296-albert">Albert</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780871139290" href="/book/show/149269.The_Inheritance_of_Loss">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18868296-albert?shelf=award-winners-read">award-winners-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18868296-albert?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/18868296-albert?shelf=award-man-booker-prize">award-man-booker-prize</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1301788874" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14174871402629486307">The Inheritance of Loss follows two concurrent stories, one of Sai, the orphan granddaughter of a retired judge, Jemubhai, and the other of Biju, the son of the cook who has worked much of his life for the judge. Sai resides in Kalimpong, an east Indian hill town in the Himalayan foothills of West Bengal, in the dilapidated mansion of the judge. Biju has escaped Kalimpong to NYC, where he works a series of jobs while trying to stay out of the grasp of the INS. The judge reflects on his past life</span>
  <span id="freeText14174871402629486307" style="display:none">The Inheritance of Loss follows two concurrent stories, one of Sai, the orphan granddaughter of a retired judge, Jemubhai, and the other of Biju, the son of the cook who has worked much of his life for the judge. Sai resides in Kalimpong, an east Indian hill town in the Himalayan foothills of West Bengal, in the dilapidated mansion of the judge. Biju has escaped Kalimpong to NYC, where he works a series of jobs while trying to stay out of the grasp of the INS. The judge reflects on his past life while Sai attempts to create a vision of a life for herself and Biju tries to find a life worth living in NYC. I found the writing in this novel beautiful and the weaving together of the hopes and regrets quite complex. <br /><br />However, I didn’t find anything new or fresh here. The focus on an aspect on Indian history leaves the impression that there will be periods of violence and the promotion of different ideas, but no fundamental change: the poor will continue to look for a way to live, to exist, and those that have something will work to protect what little they have. The complementary story of Biju as an Indian immigrant to the US that can’t find success or a place to call home in his new country just confirms that everybody is looking for a way to escape and that very few are successful. I feel that I have read these stories before. Desai tells them well, but I find I do not care for any of the characters: I am not yearning for them to achieve or accomplish or succeed. While one does not expect a novelist to solve horrific social problems that have developed over centuries, there is no glimmer of hope here, just hopelessness well-told. I have read stories that offer no hope and still enjoyed them thoroughly, but I found those stories convinced me somehow to ignore reality and to hope anyway. The Inheritance of Loss won the Booker in 2006. </span>
  <a data-text-id="14174871402629486307" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

